<paragraph id="8BC236D5FF90FFA16EE2FBDFFC79FCCA" blockId="13.[151,1437,1138,1489]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">
This is a large, endemic Chinese species with a relatively wide distribution range, including 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F837FF90FFA16AB4FBDFFA82FD96" box="[1217,1344,1138,1164]" country="China" name="Chongqing" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Chongqing</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F837FF90FFA16B3BFBDFFA5AFD96" box="[1358,1432,1138,1164]" country="China" name="Gansu" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Gansu</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F837FF90FFA16EE2FB3BFF38FDAA" box="[151,250,1174,1200]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F837FF90FFA16F70FB3BFE93FDAA" box="[261,337,1174,1200]" country="China" name="Henan" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Henan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F837FF90FFA16F29FB3BFE61FDAA" box="[348,419,1174,1200]" country="China" name="Hubei" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Hubei</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F837FF90FFA16FDBFB3BFE39FDAA" box="[430,507,1174,1200]" country="China" name="Hunan" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Hunan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F837FF90FFA16C72FB3BFD99FDAA" box="[519,603,1174,1200]" country="China" name="Jiangxi" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Jiangxi</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F837FF90FFA16C10FB3BFD00FDAA" box="[613,706,1174,1200]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F837FF90FFA16C8EFB3BFC96FDAA" box="[763,852,1174,1200]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
. The body size and color pattern are quite consistent throughout all populations. Cerci are special with the apex extended and the basal prominence long, cylindrical, foot-like (
<figureCitation id="13462A50FF90FFA16F72FB73FE8BFDE3" box="[263,329,1246,1273]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1420,1444]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,195,1385]" captionTargetId="figure-34@14.[151,1436,181,1396]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 3. Caudal appendages of males (dorsal view). a) australis; b) irma, paratype; c) distans, from Yaan, Sichuan; d) distans from Dashahe, Guizhou; e) heros; f) omeiensis, paratype; g) kurahashii; h) major; i) haui; j) “palaceus”; k) micans, bd: basal disk; l) “chengi”; m) riccii; n) “maai”; o) “tuska,” from Damingshan, Guangxi; p) “tuska,” from Jinxiu, Guangxi. (Scale bar = 0.5 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407489" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4407489/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
c–d). The end of the genital ligula has terminal lateral lobes largely divergent and up-curved at the tips (
<figureCitation id="13462A50FF90FFA16EBAFAAFFEE0FC07" box="[207,290,1282,1309]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[214,1369,199,1838]" captionTargetId="figure-34@18.[205,1381,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 5. Genital ligula of males (lateral view) (a–m) and ventral view (n–ab). a) australis; b) distans; c) heros; d) omeiensis, paratype; e) major; f) irma, paratype; g) “palaceus”; h) haui; i) “Chengi”; j) maai; k) riccii; l) tuska; m) micans; n) australis, Hr: horn; o) distans, Tlb: terminal lateral lobe; p) heros; q) omeiensis, paratype; r) major; s) irma, paratype; t) kurahashii; u) “palaceus”; v) haui; w) micans, from Jinping, Yunnan; x) “Chengi”; y) maai; z) riccii, Blb: basal lateral lobe; aa) tuska, Mlb: middle lateral lobe; ab) micans, from Fengyangshan, Zhejiang. (Scale bar = 0.2 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407495" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4407495/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Fig. 5o</figureCitation>
). The basal teeth on paraprocts varied slightly among populations (
<figureCitation id="13462A50FF90FFA16A61FAAFFB9AFC07" box="[1044,1112,1282,1309]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1443,1467]" captionTargetBox="[175,1424,244,1412]" captionTargetId="figure-56@15.[151,1437,237,1419]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 4. Caudal appendages of males (lateral view). a) australis; b) irma, paratype; c) distans, from Yaan, Sichuan; d) distans from Qingchengshan, Chengdu, Sichuan; e) heros; f) omeiensis, paratype; g) kurahashii; h) major; i) haui; j) “palaceus”; k) micans; l) “Chengi,” paratype; m) riccii; n) maai; o) tuska, from Damingshan, Guangxi; p) tuska, from Jinxiu, Guangxi. (Scale bar = 0.5 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407493" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4407493/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
c–d). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B24FF90FFA16AE2FAAFFA96FC06" author="Needham, J. G." box="[1175,1364,1282,1308]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258" pagination="227 - 231" refId="ref14437" refString="Needham, J. G. (1930) A manual of the dragonflies of China. Peiping: The Fan Memorial Institute of Biology, 227 - 231." type="book chapter" year="1930">Needham (1930)</bibRefCitation>
stated that his specimens came from both 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F837FF90FFA16C5DFA8BFD4AFC5A" box="[552,648,1318,1344]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Guangxi</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F837FF90FFA16CB5FA8BFCDCFC5A" box="[704,798,1318,1344]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
. We checked through his original descriptions and could not find any localities belonging to 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F837FF90FFA16C58FAE7FD52FC7E" box="[557,656,1354,1380]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Guangxi</collectingRegion>
, but the species is present in 
<collectingRegion id="49B9F837FF90FFA16DAAFAE7FBFBFC7E" box="[991,1081,1354,1380]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
with Yu Chi Valley as the 
<typeStatus id="54C68877FF90FFA16B19FAE7FA5EFC7E" box="[1388,1436,1354,1380]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">type</typeStatus>
locality. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B24FF90FFA16E8DFAC3FE3DFC92" author="Wilson, K. D. P. &amp; Reels, G. T." box="[248,511,1390,1416]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258" pagination="237 - 279" refId="ref15245" refString="Wilson, K. D. P. &amp; Reels, G. T. (2003) Odonata of Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, China, Part 1: Zygoptera. Odonatologica, 32, 237 - 279." type="journal article" year="2003">Wilson &amp; Reels (2003)</bibRefCitation>
