<collectingRegion id="49B9F837FF90FFA16DF5FAC3FC26FC92" box="[896,996,1390,1416]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Guangxi</collectingRegion>
. However, the figures and descriptions were not consistent with our specimens nor were they like those from 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B24FF90FFA16DCDFA3FFBBAFCB6" author="Needham, J. G." box="[952,1144,1426,1452]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258" pagination="227 - 231" refId="ref14437" refString="Needham, J. G. (1930) A manual of the dragonflies of China. Peiping: The Fan Memorial Institute of Biology, 227 - 231." type="book chapter" year="1930">Needham (1930)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B24FF90FFA16AF0FA3FFAD7FCB7" author="Chao, H. - F." box="[1157,1301,1426,1453]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258" pagination="187 - 196" refId="ref13620" refString="Chao, H. - F. (1965) A study of the Chinese dragonflies of the genus Megalestes Selys, with description of a new species (Odonata: Synlestidae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 2, 187 - 196." type="journal article" year="1965">Chao (1965)</bibRefCitation>
, or 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B24FF90FFA16B34FA3FFF27FCCB" author="Asahina, S." pageId="13" pageNumber="258" pagination="192 - 201" refId="ref13440" refString="Asahina, S. (1969) Notes on Chinese Odonata II, the Odonata of Metasequoia expedition. Kontyu, 37, 192 - 201." type="journal article" year="1969">Asahina (1969)</bibRefCitation>
. Therefore, we do not believe that 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D56FF90FFA16C1FFA1AFD1CFCCA" authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1930" box="[618,734,1462,1488]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="13" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distans">
<emphasis id="B909EAC7FF90FFA16C1FFA1AFD1CFCCA" box="[618,734,1462,1488]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">M. distans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
